<TEXT>
actor billy barty was delighted as he 
settled his 3foot9 frame into the blue and white chair 
his feet touched the ground 
how can you put a price on the smile that came across his 
face said michael buzzella vice president of sunburst outdoor 
furniture which is beginning production on one of the first 
specially designed lines for dwarfs midgets and other adults of 
small stature 
to be able to sit in a chair with your feet touching the 
ground is something averagesize people dont even think about 
buzzella said for little people its an uncommon thrill 
barty a consultant on the project said the sunburst outdoor 
furniture designs are among the first of any kind of furniture 
produced specifically for little people as he terms anyone 
afflicted by the nearly 200 different forms of dwarfism 
we are a minority that is really a minority said the 
63yearold actor in a telephone interview from tulsa okla where 
he is filming a movie we are mostly handicapped by physical 
barriers we face clothes have to be cut down light switches are 
too high 
i cant tell you how wonderful it felt like to sit in a chair 
with your feet on the ground and your back in the proper place 
added barty who has championed the little peoples cause since the 
late 1950s 
sunburst which supplies outdoor furniture to resorts and hotels 
around the world began thinking small last year with a line of 
childrens furniture for floridas walt disney world 
company founder and president rw buzzella who had built a 
scaleddown bar and stool set for a dwarf couple three years ago 
thought the childrens furniture might be adapted for the nations 
15 million little people a letter was sent in march to barty at 
his foundation for little people office in north hollywood calif 
barty quickly responded and arranged a visit to the sunburst 
production center in hialeah shortly after the release of 
willow in which he plays a high priest 
but he immediately showed us that furniture for little people 
and children are very different said michael buzzella arranging 
three chairs side by side 
the childrens chair was smaller but in the same proportions as 
the adult version the little peoples model was modified with a 
low seat and elevated armrests to accommodate their shorter limbs 
and torsos 
it was a real learning experience for us buzzella said 
you just cant put a little person in childrens furniture it 
doesnt work and they are not comfortable they have their own 
special dimensions 
sunburst a division of metaltech inc unveiled the rainbow 
collection in july at a convention in des moines iowa attended by 
about 600 little people 
buzzella took about 80 furniture orders many had special 
requests such as an extra narrow seat for a woman with a rare 
acute form of dwarfism 
the profit for sunburst in the venture is also small he said 
to be candid a big manufacturer would not touch this 
project buzzella said its not smart business its not a 
bigvolumetype deal but this company has been fortunate and wed 
like to give something back and not just think about the dollars 
involved 
sunburst which had sales of about 5 million last year scored 
a success in 1964 with the patent of an aluminum umbrella designed 
