leaked campaign strategy memos laced with 
coarse remarks threaten to ignite racial tensions in the early 
stages of a mayoral campaign that pits a jewish city councilman 
against black incumbent tom bradley 
the memos were prepared by a consulting firm associated with 
39yearold city councilman zev yaroslavsky who is seeking to 
become the citys first jewish mayor and poses by many accounts the 
first real challenge to bradley in a decade both are democrats 
the race is nonpartisan 
the documents by veteran strategists michael berman and carl 
dagostino whose firm is known as bad campaigns berate 
yaroslavsky about his grim demeanor mock bradleys intelligence 
refer to environmentalists as tree huggers and slowgrowth 
