<TEXT>
in his northern philippine stronghold 
ferdinand marcos remains a pervasive respected figure more than 
two years after a manilabased uprising toppled his 20year 
authoritarian regime 
i tell you that if he ran again he would win hands down 
here said rafael benemerito mayor of the town of pagudpud in 
the province of ilocos norte where marcos was born in 1917 you 
know we ilocanos are very clannish 
in most of the philippines the marcos years are associated with 
massive corruption economic mismanagement and oppression 
president corazon aquino has refused to allow marcos to return from 
hawaii where he fled after the february 1986 uprising that 
propelled her to power 
but in his native province marcos still enjoys widespread 
respect among his fellow ilocanos 
marcos rewarded the province which has a population of about 
440000 with roads and development projects ilocanos are strongly 
represented within the armed forces although precise figures are 
not available 
rep roque ablan a promarcos congressman says allegations of 
massive corruption and embezzlement of up to 10 billion have not 
significantly dented support for the ousted leader 
in spite of all the accusations and charges we still look up 
to mr marcos ablan said we would like to see him come home 
which is the right of every filipino 
the spirit of marcos looms over this province about 250 miles 
north of manila rural bus stops and walls of buildings in laoag 
the provincial capital still bear graffiti such as no to cory 
or marcos once more his slogan in the fraudtainted 1986 
election 
most provincial and municipal officials elected in regional 
balloting in january are members of or have been aligned with 
marcos new society movement party which has virtually 
disintegrated elsewhere in the country 
in the town hall of batac the marcos family ancestral home 
pictures of marcos and his wife imelda hang on the walls of the 
bureau of internal revenue office there is no picture of mrs 
aquino 
people here still respect mr marcos said the rev ruben 
abaya a roman catholic priest in batac they would like to see 
him come home although not necessarily as president they respect 
him for his intelligence 
promarcos politicians insist they are no longer anxious for 
marcos to return as president but as a private citizen marcos 
claimed he won the 1986 election against mrs aquino and left 
manila only after having himself sworn into office 
marcos loyalists were linked to at least three major attempts to 
topple the aquino government 
in all our conversations with mr marcos he always told us to 
cooperate with the aquino government and join hands to fight the 
communists ablan said 
but not every ilocano is a dedicated marcos loyalist communist 
rebels have made strong inroads in ilocos norte since 1981 and by 
military estimates there may be as many as 500 ilocanos in the 
communist new peoples army 
promarcos sympathies were whipped up three months ago when 
supporters of the former president spread reports he would come 
home for the funeral of his mother josefa who died may 4 
mrs aquino refused to allow him to return and the mother is 
still unburied still rumors persist that marcos will return soon 
the provinces association with marcos has not been a handicap 
under the new administration provincial gov rodolfo farinas said 
the aquino government has not discriminated against ilocos norte in 
the allocation of state funds 
but the laoag international airport which once received charter 
flights from hawaii taiwan and hong kong has been closed to 
foreign traffic since september 1986 to prevent marcos from 
slipping into the counry 
airport manager numeriano ramones said only three flights a week 
come in from manila security guards doze on the tables next to 
xray machines and goats cattle and stray dogs wander over the 
tarmac 
residents of a nearby village have erected a makeshift 
basketball court at the southeastern end of the tarmac 
the closing of the laoag airport to international traffic has 
severely curtailed business at fort ilocandia a 196room resort 
built to host the wedding reception of marcos daughter irene 
it was hoped the resort and its casino would attract high 
rollers from hong kong and filipino immigrant families from the 
united states wishing to vacation in their homeland last week the 
hotel had only three guests 
