an ordinance aimed at aggressive beggars seems to 
have reduced the number of confrontations between panhandlers and 
pedestrians but didnt prevent the death of a passerby who said no 
seattles law went into effect nov 27 after years of attempts 
by some officials and downtown businessmen alarmed by pushy 
beggars the law has served as a model for at least two other 
cities 
there has been a significant reduction in the amount of 
aggressive behavior along with panhandling said capt jim 
