services as reasons for returning to private practice she said 
budget cutbacks had left each federal judge in houston struggling 
to handle more than 1000 cases without enough employeees or 
adequate computer systems to handle the work 
sen lloyd bentsen now the democrats vice presidential 
nominee recommended mrs mcdonald for a federal judgeship when she 
was a lawyer handling employment discrimination cases 
i feel very very loyal to senator bentsen she said for 
him to appoint me when i had a reputation for suing on behalf of 
minorities that took courage 
mrs mcdonald was sworn in may 31 1979 whens she was 37 and 
became the first black and the third woman to assume a federal 
judgeship in texas 
her race came into play in several of her cases 
the grand dragon of the ku klux klan in 1981 asked her to step 
aside in a lawsuit brought by vietnamese shrimpers who claimed they 
were being harassed by klan members 
mrs mcdonald refused the request pointing out that the grand 
dragon had never heard her express a personal opinion about the 
klan 
her race became an issue again when she presided over a dispute 
about attorneys fees in a package of voting rights lawsuits 
brought against the city of houston the suits eventually led to 
changes in the way the city council is elected 
the city asked her to step down from the case in 1984 saying 
that as a black she was a plaintiff in the classaction suits filed 
on behalf of hispanic and black voters 
mrs mcdonald refused to bow out and her decision was upheld by 
the 5th us circuit court of appeals 
if the 5th circuit had not affirmed i expect i would have 
left the bench then thats how important it was she said a 
decision not to affirm would have rendered me a secondclass 
citizen 
