no one can say that well never see the likes 
of him again but ronald reagan will be a hard act for any 
president to follow 
the man actually enjoys the job 
other presidents pursued the office with equal ardor but none 
has savored it the way reagan does 
harry truman used to refer to the white house as that great 
white prison yet he had the luxury in those safer times of 
taking a walk around the block by contrast reagan is swaddled in 
a germfree cocoon and hasnt seemed to mind if he were to write a 
book you can bet it wont be about the splendid misery of it all 
that aura of comfort in the job invited a comment from delegate 
james proctor from rocky mount nc that you hear often around 
the republican national convention i dont think theres anybody 
here who wouldnt like to have ronald reagan on the ticket again 
george bush and for that matter michael dukakis eat your 
