<TEXT>
a feud between the security police and 
the governing social democratic party is proving to be an 
embarrassment to prime minister ingvar carlsson as he campaigns for 
next months general election 
in the last week the governments election worries have been 
compounded by an exchange of accusations with the secret police of 
mischiefmaking and political spying 
the feud between the government and its counterintelligence arm 
known as sapo goes back decades 
but the tension resurfaced after book publisher and former 
journalist ebbe carlsson launched his own investigation into the 
1986 assassination of prime minister olof palme 
it became clear the amateur detective an insider in the 
governing party was investigating sapo as much as looking for the 
elusive killer 
but critics said social democrats exceeded their authority and 
sidestepped official channels by ordering the secret investigation 
which has overshadowed campaign issues such as taxes or the 
environment 
justice minister annagreta leijon resigned last month after it 
was disclosed that she aided ebbe carlssons efforts to contact 
british intelligence officials for the investigation 
sapo is a department within the regular police structure and is 
responsible for ferreting out spies and protecting cabinet 
ministers 
palme who disliked the formalities of office dismissed his 
sapo bodyguards when he and his wife went to see a movie on the 
night he was killed 
prime minister carlsson not related to ebbe carlsson told a 
parliamentary inquiry aug 4 that he backed the investigation 
because of important allegations and serious criticism against a 
swedish authority 
he was referring to charges that sapo was negligent in 
protecting palme and tried to cover up its shortcomings in the hunt 
for the assassin 
ebbe carlsson told the inquiry earlier that sapo had failed to 
act on a tip that palmes life was in danger if it is not a 
conspiracy it is stupidity he told the televised hearing 
in another slap at sapo foreign minister sten andersson told 
reporters that he trusted ebbe carlsson more than he did sapos 
commanders 
palmes murder was for many leading social democrats the final 
confirmation of sapos incompetance said a report in the 
business weekly affars varlden 
holger romander a former police chief was quoted as saying the 
carlsson affair is part of a campaign against sapo by people 
who distrust an organization they cannot control and know little 
about 
social democrats say sapo is a bastion of conservative politics 
some party leaders are reported to back removal of sapo from the 
police force so that it would report directly to the government 
the svenska dagbladet newspaper said sapo urged the government 
to reject the credentials last year of a soviet diplomat whom the 
security police said was the new kgb station chief the government 
ignored their advice 
in a book published last week former sapo chief per gunnar 
vinge wrote that the social democrats created a political 
intelligence agency during the late 1950s 
the agency called the information bureau enlisted personnel in 
military or research organizations to register political opinions 
of citizens to identify communist sympathizers the book said the 
activity went on until the early 1970s 
the information bureau story was first published in 1973 and 
prime minister carlsson questioned the timing of the books 
publication six weeks before the sept 18 election 
the dispute has helped the three opposition parties cooperate in 
their attempt to unseat the social democrats who have governed 
sweden for 50 of the last 56 years 
