<TEXT>
president alfredo stroessner took the 
oath of office for an eighth time monday in a subdued ceremony that 
followed weeks of tension between the government and the roman 
catholic church 
stroessner 75 was sworn in before the congress by the 
president of the supreme court luis maria argana he then quietly 
walked off the podium without speaking to assembled representatives 
and foreign dignitaries 
the 25minute ceremony was broadcast by staterun radio across 
this landlocked and mostly rural country of 38 million 
although there were no protests the catholic church canceled 
the annual te deum mass of thanksgiving traditionally celebrated on 
aug 15 to mark the anniversary of the founding of the capital 
asuncion 
the cancellation ordered by monsignor ismael rolon archbishop 
of asuncion was a response to the expulsion july 25 of a spanish 
jesuit priest for allegedly publicly encouraging overthrow of the 
government 
the church denied the charge and said the priest juan antonio 
de la vega a 65yearold professor was explaining liberation 
theology a movement that advocates political change as a tool of 
social reform 
the church the most influential institution in the country 
after the government and the military claimed in a message 
delivered from pulpits two weeks ago that it was the victim of 
persecution 
pope john paul ii urged stroessner during a visit here last may 
to relax restrictions on human rights and political freedom 
stroessner also commander of paraguays military took power in a 
1954 coup and has ruled with a heavy hand ever since 
his tenure has brought order and modest economic growth to a 
country that had seen turmoil and 11 different presidents in the 19 
years following the end of the chaco war with bolivia in 1935 but 
most civil liberties are curtailed and dissent is crushed 
stroessner won an eighth term in february in an election marked 
by the absence of the major opposition groups and by charges of 
fraud he was credited with obtaining 886 percent of all votes 
cast 
mondays inauguration was witnessed by brazilian foreign 
minister roberto de abreu sondre taiwans prime minister yu kuo 
and delegations from south korea south africa and neighboring 
argentina 
afterward stroessner swore in his 11member cabinet rodney 
elpidio acevedo replaced carlos saldivar as foreign minister 
</TEXT>
