a conservative group pushing for a roll call 
vote for the republican vice presidential nomination lost one round 
monday when a convention committee voted to scrap the 
timeconsuming ritual to conserve television time 
however sen gordon humphrey rnh chairman of the group 
calling itself the coalition for a winning ticket said that he 
