putting up a rival candidate for vice president to keep the process 
open 
every dictator in history has wanted to make the trains run on 
time humphrey said at a news conference after his proposal died 
before the republican national conventions rules committee 
there is no more foolish thing in politics than seeking to stifle 
dissent 
humphrey has been outspoken in recent weeks in urging george 
bush to choose a conservative as his vice presidential running 
mate bush has not said who he will ask to join him on the ticket 
now humphrey and his group object to a rules change that would 
dispense with a statebystate roll call vote on the gop vice 
