<TEXT>
tens of thousands of people turned 
the funeral for threetime president arnulfo arias madrid into a 
huge but peaceful antigovernment demonstration monday 
it was one of the largest demonstrations in 14 months of 
protests against the rule of gen manuel antonio noriega who 
commands panamas defense forces and controls the civilian 
government 
arias was elected three times and overthrown each time by the 
military he died wednesday in miami 
arias who would would have been 87 monday spent more time in 
jail and exile than in office but was credited with founding 
panamas social security system and introducing womens suffrage 
a vast crowd gathered in the plaza in front of the metropolitan 
cathedral for the funeral that was conducted from the church steps 
as the service ended and the coffin was placed aboard a 
firetruck a roar went up from the crowd with the people repeatedly 
shouting justice 
thousands of people followed the cortege out of the plaza 
through the narrow streets of the old section of panama city and 
onto central avenue for the threemile journey to a cemetery with 
each block te procession became longer until people filled the 
fourlane avenue for nearly a mile 
arnulfo president noriega criminal people in the crowd 
shouted noriega must go 
many people waved white banners a sign of protest in panama or 
the flags of political parties opposed to noriega who was indicted 
by two federal grand juries in florida last february on charges of 
narcotics trafficking 
the government offered to provide military honors at the funeral 
but the authentic panamanian party which arias founded in 1935 
refused instead the party decided on the requiem mass conducted 
on the cathedral steps by marcos mcgrath the roman catholic 
archbishop 
we cant accept that those who always overthrew the doctor 
arias share in our grief said francisco artola party vice 
president the ceremony is going to be for the people 
noriegas soldiers and police who have crushed dozens of 
protests in the past 14 months did not interfere with the funeral 
despite the antigovernment tone 
firefighters helped control the cathedral crowd and one of their 
bright orange ladder trucks carried the flagdraped coffin to the 
garden of peace cemetery 
all sides in this politically divided country claimed arias as 
their own 
governmentcontrolled newspapers referred vaguely to his 
errors during 57 years in politics but praised his nationalism 
and defiance of the united states 
us ambassador arthur davis and his daughter susan were among 
the mourners monday 
arias was first turned out of office by a military coup july 14 
1941 after serving 9 months of a fouryear term in january of 
that year he had rejected a us war department request for land 
for military bases along the panama canal 
soon after arias was deposed at washingtons urging panama 
provided 37000 acres for the bases 
he was elected again in 1949 but tossed out by the army in 1951 
he began his third elected term oct 1 1968 but was overthrown 11 
days later in a coup led by gen omar torrijos whom noriega 
replaced as head of the 15000member defense forces 
four years ago arias ran for president again and lost to nicolas 
ardito barletta noriegas candidate in an election widely viewed 
as fraudulent the government said ardito barletta won by 1713 
votes 
arias died of a heart attack he had gone to florida for medical 
treatment last april and remained there until his death 
</TEXT>
