manabua mabe artist born in japan in 1924 mabe immigrated to 
brazil with his parents in 1935 after 10 years of picking coffee 
beans he started painting figurative art but soon moved to 
abstractionist paintings his first public recognition as an artist 
came in 1957 when he won the best national painter award at the sao 
paulo bienal international art exhibition two years later he was 
awarded the best foreign painter award at the paris bienal art 
show mabe has a studio in new york but continues to paint at his 
home in sao paulo exhibiting his work in brazil and abroad 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
tomie ohtake artist born in japan in 1914 she came to brazil 
in 1936 to visit relatives but decided to stay after the 
sinojapanese war broke out in 1937 and falling in love with 
agronomist ruy ohtake whom she married she started painting as a 
hobby but friends and relatives insisted she go public and in 1957 
she exhibited her work at sao paulos museum of modern art in 
september she will have a onewoman show in japan one of many 
countries where her paintings can be found 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
fujio tachibana banker he came to brazil as a 20yearold in 
1932 to work on a coffee plantation because of his training as an 
accountant he landed a job in 1938 with the bratac banking house 
that two years later became the america do sul bank one of 
brazils largest he became president in 1978 and still holds that 
prestigious position 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
hiro hi urushima entrepreneur he was 11 years old when he 
arrived in brazil with his parents and seven brothers in 1936 like 
most other japanese immigrants he worked on a coffee plantation 
but in 1938 his family left the plantation and urushima went to 
work in a radio repair shop in the city of sao paulo in the 1940s 
he started his own business building transformers and radio 
receivers in 1954 he began building car radios and selling them to 
stores and individuals nine years later he founded motoradio 
which today employs more than 2000 workers at three different 
factories making table and car radios as well as a wide variety of 
electronic components 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
