<TEXT>
inflation as measured by consumer prices 
rose last spring in the united states and its main trading 
partners according to a central intelligence agency report made 
available monday 
the cias directorate of intelligence found that while us 
inflation fell from 37 percent in 1987 to an annualized rate of 
34 percent in the first quarter it rose in the marchjune period 
to 48 percent 
canadas inflation rate fell from a 44 percent rate last year 
to 32 percent in the first quarter but also picked up in the 
second quarter to 5 percent the report said 
britain had a 41 percent inflation rate in 1987 the level 
dropped to 24 percent in the first quarter and rose to 61 percent 
in the second quarter the report said 
among other major industrialized nations tracked in the cia 
report japans firstquarter inflation rate fell by 21 percent 
from a 01 percent rate in 1987 but rose to 28 percent in the 
second quarter 
west germanys 1987 inflation of 03 percent doubled to 06 
percent in the first quarter and rose to 19 percent in the spring 
the rise was less marked in france and italy countries more 
usually inclined to inflation the french rate of 28 percent in 
the second quarter of 1988 was an increase over the winter rate of 
23 percent but still below the 33 percent of 1987 
in italy the rate was 46 percent in 1987 after falling 
steadily since the 149 percent level of 1983 it was down to 31 
percent in the first quarter of this year but then rose again to 
45 percent in the second three months 
the cias twicemonthly economic and energy indicators for 
july 29 did not provide figures for smaller countries 
the international monetary fund which does says inflation on 
the consumer level among 21 industrial countries rose to an 
annualized rate of 3 percent in may from 29 percent of 1987 
the imf said the average inflation level for 116 other 
countries mostly in the third world was 398 percent in 1987 it 
increased to a rate of 557 percent in january however few figures 
for later months were available 
financial authorities have been especially worried about brazil 
with the biggest economy in latin america and the biggest debt in 
the third world the imf reported brazilian inflation at more than 
229 percent last year and rising at an annual rate of just under 
500 percent in april 
argentinas rate was 131 percent in 1987 having risen steadily 
throughout the year according to the imf it has been reported 
rising since but the fund had no 1988 figures for argentina in its 
statistics for august 
south korea on the other hand has been keeping its rate below 
3 percent in recent years although it reached that level in 1987 
and reported an annual rate of 74 percent this june the imf said 
bolivia where the inflation rate hit a high of 11750 percent 
in 1985 was down to 15 percent last year and has been reporting 
between 8 percent and 9 percent in 1988 the imf said 
the current inflation frontrunner among the imfs members is 
nicaragua with an annual rate of more than 3766 percent in june 
